Create `apps/client/src/layers/features/agents-list/ui/AgentFilterBar.tsx` — a filter bar with search input, status chips, namespace dropdown, result count, and group-by toggle.

## Component Interface

```tsx
interface AgentFilterBarProps {
  agents: AgentManifest[];
  onFilterChange: (filtered: AgentManifest[]) => void;
}
```

Import `AgentManifest` from `@dorkos/shared/mesh-schemas`.

## Internal State

The filter bar manages its own state and calls `onFilterChange` with the filtered result whenever any filter changes:

```tsx
const [searchQuery, setSearchQuery] = useState('');
const [statusFilter, setStatusFilter] = useState<'all' | 'active' | 'inactive' | 'stale'>('all');
const [namespaceFilter, setNamespaceFilter] = useState<string>('all');
const [groupByNamespace, setGroupByNamespace] = useState(false);
```

Derive health status from agent data. The status filter applies client-side — compute health status for each agent based on the `useMeshAgentHealth` hook data (or accept a `healthMap` prop mapping agent IDs to health status).

Alternative approach: Accept a `healthStatusMap: Record<string, 'active' | 'inactive' | 'stale'>` prop so the parent can compute health once and pass it down.

## Filter Logic (useMemo)

```tsx
const filtered = useMemo(() => {
  let result = agents;

  // Text search — matches name, description, capabilities
  if (searchQuery.trim()) {
    const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase();
    result = result.filter(
      (a) =>
        a.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||
        (a.description?.toLowerCase().includes(q) ?? false) ||
        a.capabilities.some((c) => c.toLowerCase().includes(q))
    );
  }

  // Status filter
  if (statusFilter !== 'all') {
    result = result.filter((a) => healthStatusMap[a.id] === statusFilter);
  }

  // Namespace filter
  if (namespaceFilter !== 'all') {
    result = result.filter((a) => a.namespace === namespaceFilter);
  }

  return result;
}, [agents, searchQuery, statusFilter, namespaceFilter, healthStatusMap]);
```

Call `onFilterChange(filtered)` in a `useEffect` whenever `filtered` changes.

## UI Elements

Layout: `<div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3">`

1. **Search input**: `<Input />` from `@/layers/shared/ui/input` with `Search` icon from lucide-react as a prefix. Placeholder: `"Filter agents..."`. Instant filtering via `onChange`. Sizing: `className="h-8 w-48 text-sm"`.

2. **Status chips**: Mutually exclusive toggle group using `<Button variant="outline" size="sm">` for each option: All (default), Active, Inactive, Stale. Active chip gets `variant="default"` or a `bg-accent` class. Implementation:
   ```tsx
   {(['all', 'active', 'inactive', 'stale'] as const).map((status) => (
     <Button
       key={status}
       variant={statusFilter === status ? 'default' : 'outline'}
       size="sm"
       className="h-7 px-2.5 text-xs capitalize"
       onClick={() => setStatusFilter(status)}
     >
       {status}
     </Button>
   ))}
   ```

3. **Namespace dropdown**: `<Select />` from `@/layers/shared/ui/select`. Only rendered when agents span >1 unique namespace. Options: "All namespaces" (value: `'all'`) + each unique namespace derived from `agents.map(a => a.namespace).filter(Boolean)`.
   ```tsx
   const namespaces = useMemo(() => [...new Set(agents.map((a) => a.namespace).filter(Boolean))], [agents]);
   {namespaces.length > 1 && (
     <Select value={namespaceFilter} onValueChange={setNamespaceFilter}>
       <SelectTrigger className="h-8 w-40 text-xs">
         <SelectValue placeholder="All namespaces" />
       </SelectTrigger>
       <SelectContent>
         <SelectItem value="all">All namespaces</SelectItem>
         {namespaces.map((ns) => (
           <SelectItem key={ns} value={ns}>{ns}</SelectItem>
         ))}
       </SelectContent>
     </Select>
   )}
   ```

4. **Result count**: `<span className="text-muted-foreground text-xs">{filtered.length} agents</span>` — updates instantly as filters change.

5. **Group-by toggle**: `<Button variant="ghost" size="sm">` with `Layers` icon. Default: flat list for single namespace, grouped for >1 namespace. Toggle button flips `groupByNamespace` state. Pass grouping state up via `onFilterChange` or a separate `onGroupChange` callback.

